<p>I was excited when I heard Angular 2 would support server-side rendering with since SEO was a huge
PITA (pain in the ass) with Angular 1. It was said that server-side rendering would be possible through Angular Universal.
</p>

<p>
Yet, this Angular Universal thing, what's up with that? Seems to have a really small team on that
and there doesn't really seem to be any documentation. Well at least there's a getting started repo, so I thought.
However, this repo
(<a href="https://github.com/robwormald/ng-universal-demo">https://github.com/robwormald/ng-universal-demo</a>)
doesn't even have a readme...
</p>

<p>
Also, when you check out some of those files, they don't seem very professional. For example:
<a href="https://github.com/robwormald/ng-universal-demo/blob/master/src/express-engine.ts">https://github.com/robwormald/ng-universal-demo/blob/master/src/express-engine.ts</a>
</p>

<p>
First line of code: <code>//hacky express wrapper thingy</code>.
</p>

