<p>
Seriously?
</p>

<p>
Then of course, there's also some confusion as to where to go and look for resources. You'll find quite a few.
</p>

<p>


When you just google "Angular Universal" (as of May 2017) you'll get to <a href="https://universal.angular.io/">https://universal.angular.io/</a>.

However, this page is a bit out of date.

</p>

<p>
Just have a look at the date:

