<br>

Angular 2 is now Angular 4 and <code>--ambient</code> is also not a thing anymore. So the only purpose of universal.angular.io is
to confuse people with outdated material and to link to github (<a href="https://github.com/angular/universal">https://github.com/angular/universal</a>).

</p>

<p>

Github, even though being the best resource on Angular Universal, isn't really documented either. Meh.
</p>


<p>
Well, I guess switching to React isn't such a bad idea after all?
